SHELL (Fig. 49; 
Tables 3–4
). Depressed conical, with 5.25–6 hardly convex whorls; protoconch almost smooth; teleoconch with fine, irregular wrinkles; apical side with indistinct incised spiral lines, umbilical side with more distinct spiral lines and a granular sculpture; scaly processes sparse, mainly at periphery; tuberculate around umbilicus; brownish-corneous; body whorl keeled; aperture rounded rhombic; upper insertion of peristome descending; peristome expanded, reflexed and thickened; umbilicus slightly eccentric, wide, comprising 32–40% of shell diameter, hardly obscured by columellar edge.
